    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>IN
                    <lb n="2"/>MEMORY OF
                    <lb n="3"/><listRelation><relation name="husband" xml:id="Husband"><desc>MY DEAR HUSBAND</desc></relation></listRelation>
                    <lb n="4"/><persName xml:id="Theophilus_George_Ayres">THEOPHILUS GEORGE AYRES</persName>
                    <lb n="5"/><desc>WHO DIED <date type="death" when="1935-07-30"><date xml:id="July">JULY</date> 30TH 1935</date></desc>, <date type="age" subtype="death" dur="P80Y">AGED 80 YEARS</date>
                    <lb n="6"/>ALSO OF
                    <lb n="7"/><persName xml:id="Eliza_Ayres">ELIZA AYRES</persName>
                    <lb n="8"/><listRelation><relation name="wife" xml:id="Wife"><desc>WIFE OF THE ABOVE</desc></relation></listRelation>
                    <lb n="9"/><desc>WHO DIED <date type="death" when="1950-12-16"><date xml:id="December">DECEMBER</date> 16TH 1950</date></desc>
                    <lb n="10"/><date type="age" subtype="death" dur="P94Y">AGED 94 YEARS</date>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>In memory of my dead husband, Theophilus George Ayres, who died July 30th 1935, aged 80 years.
                   Also of Eliza Ayres, wife of the above, who died December 16th 1950, aged 94 years.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This twentieth century gravestone lists the names of <num xml:id="Two">two</num> occupants, Theophilus George Ayres and Eliza Ayres. 
                   From the age and the date of death, we can calculate that Theophilus George Ayres would have been born c. 1855 and Eliza Ayres would have been born c. 1856.
                   Its location within the churchyard is at the back of the church, three rows of graves back from the entrance to the belfry.</p>
            </div>
